column2: Poor weather-  no sun for two weeks and rain.
Calm today. very little rain- lots of wind.
Partly cloudy and the weed harvesting to start on 6/29.
Temp. 60- cloudy to partly cloudy- calm conditions.
Temperature 50 F- NW wind @ 10 mph- clear sky.
Weed harvest to start 7/5/88- air temp. 81 F- water temp. 78 F.
Weed harvest completed 7/13- color improving- air 84 F- water 82 F.
Air temp. 62 F- water temp. 55 F.
Ice off 4/17- water temperature 60 F @ 4 ft.
Water temperature. @ 5 ft. 64 F- weeds progressing nicely.
Water temp. @ 5 ft. 76 F- color starting to get green.
Green algae mostly gone- water temp. @ 5' 70 F.
Early variety weed very prominent in some areas.
Water cloudy- rain all day yesterday.
Weedy in some areas- 3-4" of rain in last week.
6" of rain past week- weed harvesting done in channels- dam repair to start soon- no lowering of river expected.
Apple River Dam in Amery under repair now.  No drawdown is expected.
Ice off 3 weeks ago.  Windy- water cloudy from rain storms.
Weeds up in bays + edges of channel.
Water is clearer due to heavy rains last week- duckweed not as thick as last month.
Week of hot weather followed by 3" of rain.
Shore line weeds- duck weeds- water is clear due to heavy rains.
Heavy rains have kept the flowage clear but this has also led to heavy weed growth.
Heavy weed growth- mostly northern milfoil.
Heavy weed growth in water under 10 feet.
River is 14-16 inches low due to lack of rain.
Warm fall.  Water still 59 degrees.  Two inches of rain yesterday.
Early ice out on 3/29/98.  Water is warm and fish are in the shallows.
Late ice-off 4/21. A very high water spring.
Water very brown in color. Sunfish die off observed.
Heavy rains week before.  River level very high and dark.
Bass spawning- green moss on surface.
Thick curry pondweed.  Heavy rain days before.
Heavy weed growth with thick layer of duckweed on upper flowage.
Thick weeds- coontail and duckweed.  Heavy rain upstream week before.
very thick weeds and duck weeds
looks like a swamp; very heavy coontail and duckweed.
heavy coon tail and duck weed - north end
heavy rain week before. thick duck weed.
